JOHN PRESTON; AUTHOR, FORMER EDITOR OF GAY MAGAZINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Preston, 48, co-founder of one of the nation's first gay community 
centers and a former editor of the Advocate, the nation's largest gay 
magazine.Preston helped found Gay House Inc. in Minneapolis and moved to San 
Francisco in 1975 to serve as editor of the Advocate. He wrote more than 40 
books, including "The Big Gay Book: A Man's Survival Guide for the '90s," 
"Hometowns: Gay Men Write About Where They Belong" and "Franny, the Queen of 
Provincetown." In Portland, Me., on Wednesday of the complications of AIDS. 
