<HEADLINE>
<P>
POPCORN IN THEATERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Popcorn is not only a hazard to your health but to the aesthetic enjoyment of 
a movie. When we go to a live play in a theater, we don't have to cope with the 
rancid stench of popcorn oil, the crunching of teeth, the smacking of lips. 
That's why my family stays away from movie theaters and rents videos. 
</P>
<P>
 G. BORDING MATHIEU 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA043094-0042 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 037175 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
