<P>
 Rancho Alamitos 5, Pacifica 0 -- Freshman Taylor Yandell pitched a four-hit 
shutout, striking out 10, and Tommy Garcia, Brett Osterode and Tony Luce each 
had two hits for host Rancho Alamitos (5-13, 2-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 3, Orange Lutheran -- Alex Okland's two-out single in the 
bottom of the seventh drove in Kenny Nash with the winning run for host Calvary 
Chapel (12-7, 4-3). Okland had all three RBIs for the Eagles. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 5, Newport Harbor 0 -- Tony Zuniga pitched a two-hitter, striking 
out nine, for his first shutout. Zuniga was also three for four, scored two 
runs and drove in a run for host Saddleback (12-9-1, 6-4). Newport is 3-16, 
0-10. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 11, Dana Hills 0 -- Ryan Gauntner, Brandon Puffer and Paul 
Day hit home runs and Brian Harnetiaux was three for four as Capistrano Valley 
(14-7, 6-5) moved into a tie for second place with Dana Hills (11-10-1, 6-5) 
and El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley touched Dana Hills starter Seth Etherton (7-1) for seven 
runs in four innings. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 9, San Clemente 3 -- Third baseman Justo Capacete went two for two, 
scored twice, had three RBIs and two stolen bases for El Toro (14-8, 6-5). Ryan 
Fullerton got two hits during the seven-run fifth inning for the Chargers. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 11, Mission Viejo 2 -- Matt Treanor had three hits, including a home 
run, three runs scored and two RBIs for the Monarchs (15-5-1, 10-1). Erik 
Mattern also had two hits, a home run, two runs scored and four RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Harris had a perfect game entering the fifth inning, before giving up a 
walk and a hit. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 4, Westminster 3 -- The Chargers scored three runs in the third inning 
on a Greg Hanoian two-run double and Tommy Barilla single to take the lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Todd Belitz pitched five scoreless innings for Edison (14-7, 5-5), striking 
out eight and giving up two hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 3, Marina 1 -- Dan Hoppie hit a home run for No. 1 Fountain 
Valley (20-2, 8-2). Kevin Burford added a two-run double in the first. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 4, Ocean View 3 -- Santa Ana broke its 22-game league losing streak 
by defeating visiting Ocean View. Jesus Rodarte was two for two, scored one run 
and had one RBI for the Saints (5-15, 1-8). 
</P>
