<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN KLAIR WINS FEATURE AT HOLLYPARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden Klair rallied from 13 lengths off the pace to win the $102,900 A Gleam 
Handicap on the first of 13 Friday nights of racing at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Chris McCarron and trained by Darrell Vienna, Golden Klair overtook 
9-10 favorite Cargo in mid-stretch to win the seven-furlong race by two 
lengths. 
</P>
<P>
 Cargo, ridden by Gary Stevens, finished second, six lengths in front of 
Minidar. Tour was fourth and last. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second win in as many starts at Hollywood Park for Golden Klair, a 
four-year-old who won the Silver Belles last Dec. 5. Golden Klair paid $7.80 
and $2.80. Show wagering was canceled after Southern Truce and Desert Stormer 
were scratched. 
</P>
</TEXT>
