<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; IRVINE SWIMMERS DEFEAT VILLA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Irvine girls' relay teams were the deciding factor in its 159-133 victory 
over Villa Park in a nonleague swim meet Friday at Heritage Park in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Wendy O'Brien, who has the county's fastest times in the 50 and 100 
freestyles this season, anchored the 200 and 400 freestyle relays for Irvine 
(9-2). The Vaqueros won the 200 medley relay in 1:56.77. 
</P>
<P>
 Tea Lindberg won the 200 individual medley (2:24.59) and 100 breaststroke 
(1:11.76) for Villa Park (8-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague girls' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 99, Cypress 69 -- Nicole Luque won the 200 individual medley (2:33.7) 
and 100 breaststroke (1:19.2) for visiting Canyon (10-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 111, Tustin 51 -- Miranda Lim won the 100 (1:01.52) and 200 freestyle 
(2:13.06) for Foothill's (4-1 in league).  
</P>
<P>
 In boys' nonleague swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 99, Tustin 70 -- Jim Lowe won the 50 (22.60) and 500 freestyle 
(5:00.48) for the Tillers. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 156, Irvine 134 -- Matt Cornue won the 200 freestyle (1:44.76) and 
100 butterfly (55.30) as Villa Park (10-0) finished its third undefeated 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 In boys' Century League tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 14, Orange 7 -- Canyon's (12-4, 5-3) doubles team of Warren Wang and 
Andy Choi improved their overall record to 26-7, sweeping their sets, 6-4, 7-5, 
6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 16 2/3, El Dorado 4 1/3 -- The doubles teams of Adriano 
Satele-Steve Abdelmalek and Joe Shih-Herbert Manansala swept their sets for 
visiting Los Alamitos (13-3, 6-1). Satele and Abdelmalek won 6-3, 6-4, 6-0. 
Shih and Manansala won 6-2, 6-2, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 11, Brea-Olinda 10 -- Chris Tobolski won two of his three singles 
sets, 6-3, 2-6, 6-2 for Valencia (13-7, 6-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Western 18 1/3, Savanna 2 2/3 -- Dean Ras and Danh Dao swept at No. 1 doubles 
for Western, 6-0, 6-1, 6-2. Western improved to 9-7, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
