<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: MATER DEI PITCHER HARRIS SIGNS WITH STANFORD BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mater Dei right-hander Adam Harris has signed a letter of intent to play for 
Stanford, Monarch Coach Bob Ickes said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Harris, 7-0 with a county-leading earned-run average of 0.45, also considered 
Harvard and Dartmouth. Harris pitched a no-hitter in the Monarchs' 11-0 South 
Coast League rout of San Clemente on April 15.  
</P>
<P>
 Harris has a 4.6 grade-point average (on a 4.0 scale), Ickes said. JASON H. 
REID 
</P>
