<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ethan Taub, the Foothill sprinter who has the county's top 800-meters time 
this season (1 minute 55.05 seconds), has signed a letter of intent to attend 
California, he said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Taub, one of the state's finest 400-meter runners, participated as a member of 
the U.S. contingency to last summer's Maccabiah Games in Jerusalem.After a 
fifth-place finish in the open 400 meters, he ran a leg for the victorious 
1,600-meter relay team. 
</P>
<P>
 At last year's state final, his 400-meters time of 48.99 was good for seventh 
place. 
</P>
<P>
 Don Oliver, a teammate of Taub's at Foothill, signed Friday with UC Santa 
Barbara, Gaucho assistant coach Marc Kallick said. 
</P>
<P>
 Oliver, who was the 400-meter runner-up at Saturday's Orange County 
Championships in the county's second-best time this season (48.57), also has 
the county's second-best 110 high hurdles time (14.7) and fourth-best 300 
intermediate hurdles time (39.1). MATT FARMER 
</P>
