175 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NITTY-GRITTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Keep track of clean or dirty dishes in dishwasher. Place an empty spice jar 
with the lid off in corner of top rack.Container will be full of water if 
dishes are clean. Empty and get ready for next load. 
</P>
<P>
 * Clean wooden kitchen cabinets with a solution of 10 parts water and 1 part 
ammonia. When dry, apply a thin coat of wax. 
</P>
<P>
 * Eliminate odors from laundry hamper. Sprinkle baking soda between each layer 
of soiled clothing, such as sports uniforms. A 1/2-cup of baking soda added to 
rinse cycle when laundering will also help remove odors. 
</P>
<P>
 * Protect toddler's hands when playing on swing sets. Cover swing-set chains 
with plastic shower-rod covers to prevent pinched fingers. 
</P>
<P>
 * Remove light stains on marble tabletops. Sprinkle salt on a lemon slice and 
rub gently over area. Be careful not to dull polished surface. Remove residue 
with soap and water. 
</P>
<P>
 * In the yard, divert attention from eyesores such as air conditioning units. 
Plant loosely pruned evergreens and flowering perennials around structure so it 
blends into landscape. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
