<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOFT SEATING FOR CUSHY COMFORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Couch-potato alert. The High Point, N.C., spring furniture market, which ended 
last week, produced a new upholstery fabric for those who like a cushy seat. 
</P>
<P>
 Polarfleece, that fuzzy stuff popular for lightweight jackets and weekend 
sportswear, is the latest fabric to make the jump from fashion to home 
furnishings. 
</P>
<P>
 It showed up on a modern version of a blue wing chair at the Milling Road 
division of Baker Furniture and is available in red, gray, khaki and brown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
