<HEADLINE>
<P>
ITALY SEEKS GRAFT TRIAL FOR BERLUSCONI'S BROTHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Italian magistrates asked Friday that the brother of Prime Minister-designate 
Silvio Berlusconi and 29 others, including former government leader Bettino 
Craxi, be brought to trial on corruption charges. 
</P>
<P>
 The request followed a probe into alleged bribes paid on property deals with 
Italy's biggest savings bank, Cariplo. The probe erupted in the midst of Silvio 
Berlusconi's election campaign. 
</P>
<P>
 A senior judge must rule whether there is sufficient ground to try the 30 on 
charges of corruption and receiving bribes. 
</P>
<P>
 Paolo Berlusconi, who runs the family property businesses, was briefly 
arrested shortly before his brother's conservative Freedom Alliance won a 
general election held March 27 and 28. He denies any wrongdoing. 
</P>
