L.A. FIESTA BROADWAY DETOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The fifth L.A. Fiesta Broadway will be held Downtown Sunday from 11 a.m. to 6 
p.m. The free event features more than 70 entertainers, 250 food booths, games 
and exhibitions.Vehicular traffic will be prohibited from Temple Street to 11th 
Street beginning at 9 tonight. Other streets shown will be rerouted in the 
affected area, with most of the changes in effect from 9 p.m. Saturday to 5 
a.m. Monday. The Metro Red Line will extend service on Sunday until 10 p.m. For 
transit information, call (213) 626-4455. 
