</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County runners are invited to participate in their own "Run for the 
Roses," a 6K benefit run, Sunday at Mile Square Regional Park in Fountain 
Valley to kick off Kentucky Derby Week. 
</P>
<P>
 The race will begin at 8:30 a.m. At 9:30, a 10-furlong "fun run" will be 
held.The 1 1/4 miles is the same distance covered by thoroughbreds in the 
Kentucky Derby. 
</P>
<P>
 There are no entry fees to participate. T-shirts will be sold for $10 each, 
with proceeds benefiting youth athletics. 
</P>
<P>
 More than $2,000 in prizes will be awarded in drawings after the race. In 
keeping with the Derby Day theme, runners will be given red roses as they cross 
the finish line.  
</P>
<P>
 Booths offering food, drinks and health-oriented information will also be 
featured. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sponsored by Silky Sullivan's Restaurant & Irish Pub, which has 
been putting on the "Run for the Roses" for 10 years. The restaurant will hold 
Kentucky Derby Day festivities May 7. 
</P>
<P>
 More information is available by calling the restaurant at (714) 963-2718. 
