<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. RELIGION NOTES / DAYE CLARK: DAY OF PRAYER OBSERVANCES PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The National Day of Prayer will be observed Thursday throughout the county. 
The theme this year is "Heal Our Land." The Orange County Coordinating 
Committee '94 and LOVE, in the Name of Christ of Southern Orange County will 
have a program from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m. at the Plaza of the Flags square, behind 
the Santa Ana Courthouse, 700 Civic Center Drive West.The program will include 
worship services and readings from the Old and New Testaments. From noon to 
2:30 p.m., there will be a prayer convocation, with churches and public 
officials from throughout the county participating. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of the countywide observance, "Concerts of Prayer" rallies will be 
held from 7:30 to 9 p.m. at the following churches: Victory Christian Center, 
8932 Katella Ave., Anaheim; Vineyard Christian Fellowship, 5340 E. La Palma 
Ave., Anaheim; Newport Vineyard Christian Fellowship, 102 E. Baker St., Costa 
Mesa; Garden Grove Friends Church, 12211 Magnolia Ave., Garden Grove; Community 
United Methodist Church, 6662 Heil Ave., Huntington Beach; La Habra Christian 
Church, 1400 Bella Vista Drive, La Habra Heights; Saddleback Community Church, 
1 Saddleback Parkway, Lake Forest; First Southern Baptist Church, 840 N. 
Shattuck Place, Orange and Grand Avenue United Methodist Church, 2121 N. Grand 
Ave., Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 As in past years, there will be a gathering at noon at the Costa Mesa City 
Hall flagpole, 77 Fair Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove area churches have planned a continental breakfast and prayer at 
the Garden Grove Community Center from 6:45 to 8 a.m. at 11300 Stanford Ave. 
Information: (714) 252-1035. 
</P>
